Great Chief Shen carried you home

286
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:42,760
in his arms in front of everyone.

287
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,000
Do you expect him

288
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,480
to stand by and let me die?

289
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:49,720
Listen to yourself.

290
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:51,240
You never say anything sweet.

291
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:53,680
So sharp-tongued.

292
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:54,760
Listen to you.

293
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,600
There's nothing you wouldn't say.

294
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,920
So reckless.

295
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:00,600
Look at you.

296
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,280
You just returned to the mansion

297
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:05,840
and you're already glowing.

298
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,080
Let me see.

299
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,600
What tricks did they play

300
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,640
to make your eyes

301
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:13,840
so bright and spirited?

302
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,280
Well…

303
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:18,200
You don't say.

304
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,080
I fell asleep as soon as

305
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:21,680
I laid down last night.

306
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:25,240
Could it be that I've gotten used
to sleeping with the lights on

307
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:28,560
in the Shen Mansion?

308
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,480
On the contrary,

309
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,800
I couldn't sleep here.

310
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,240
Alright.

311
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:35,560
I'm serious.

312
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:40,898
[Shen Mansion]

313
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,600
This is…

314
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,760
My savior.

315
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:47,040
To repay your kindness,

316
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,120
I've prepared dishes

317
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:51,720
that could help your eyes recover.

318
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,400
From now on,

319
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:56,000
you have to keep a healthy diet
with no exception.

320
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,240
I will cook for you until you recover.

321
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:04,160
Why aren't you eating?

322
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,320
Could it be

323
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:08,840
that you're picky with food?

324
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:12,240
Or you don't want to eat?

325
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,200
I made these out of goodwill.

326
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,120
Don't waste the food.

327
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:19,912
I'll leave you to eat.

328
00:19:23,447 --> 00:19:27,265
♫ One glance affirms the fate between us ♫

329
00:19:27,265 --> 00:19:30,942
♫ Upon meeting again,
I know you're the one for me ♫

330
00:19:30,942 --> 00:19:36,160
♫ Gaze at the stars,
dreaming about the old times ♫

331
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:38,455
What's the rush, honey?

332
00:19:38,455 --> 00:19:42,882
♫ Before the candlelight,
do not ask my thoughts ♫

333
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,520
Since when

334
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:46,840
do you need someone

335
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,040
to keep you company over meals?

336
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:54,040
But you cooked for me.

337
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:57,495
I'll enjoy the food better in your presence.

338
00:19:57,495 --> 00:20:00,823
♫ I share the autumn moon
and spring breeze only with you ♫

339
00:20:00,823 --> 00:20:02,423
♫ Your palm lines ♫

340
00:20:02,423 --> 00:20:05,680
♫ Your gaze ♫

341
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,800
Like I said,

342
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,680
what's the rush, honey?

343
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,400
You're a grown-up.

344
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,560
Do you still

345
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:15,360
need someone to feed you?

346
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:18,271
♫ Your palm lines ♫

347
00:20:18,271 --> 00:20:20,822
♫ Your gaze ♫

348
00:20:20,822 --> 00:20:23,595
♫ Our love is deepening ♫

349
00:20:23,595 --> 00:20:28,337
♫ You are the one for me ♫

350
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:33,840
I can totally sense your goodwill.

351
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:38,760
Honey, please dig in.

352
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,640
From now on,

353
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:57,160
always join me for meals.

354
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,960
Do you agree?

355
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,200
I depend on you for a living.

356
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,440
Do I even have a choice?

357
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:10,360
Good that you know.

358
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:21,440
What's wrong?

359
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,200
You have no table manners.

360
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,200
That's not true.

361
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,600
I have manners.

362
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,960
What's going on?

363
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,880
What a loving couple.

364
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,640
Others can only be envious.

365
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,760
This must be what it's like

366
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,880
to be inseparable.

367
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,680
I just don't know

368
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:47,960
how long they can stay like this.

369
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,120
Every grievance has a source.

370
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,160
Don't come after me.

371
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:00,080
Don't come after me.

372
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,240
It wasn't me.

373
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:03,800
Don't come after me.

374
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,880
It wasn't me.

375
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:15,880
Don't come after me.

376
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:19,432
Don't come after me.

377
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:48,800
Great Chief, when we arrived,

378
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,480
we found him tied up to the eaves.

379
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:51,920
We waited for you

380
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:54,880
lest we destroy the crime scene.

381
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,080
Great Chief.

382
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,240
Chen Shoujie survived.

383
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:02,440
The guards we sent to protect him
saved him in time.

384
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,840
But it seems that he has been quite shocked.

385
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,560
He's been acting crazy all along.

386
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,760
Now he can't even speak

387
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:10,120
a complete sentence.

388
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,800
It looks just like the Furong Garden.

389
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,360
Back then, Han Shiyuan and Caiwei

390
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:16,720
were also tied up and hung midair

391
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,600
with fires burning beneath them.

392
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,720
But it was the cold flame

393
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:21,680
of the jugglers from the Western Regions.

394
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:22,960
This looks like

395
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:25,440
a real attempted murder.

396
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:28,480
Who on earth

397
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,520
would want to murder Chen Shoujie

398
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:33,360
in such a cruel way?

399
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:37,640
Let's go.

400
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,440
How did the Chen Mansion get burned?

401
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,520
How tragic!

402
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:53,560
Who is that? Why is he hiding?

403
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:56,000
Jing Lin.

404
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,680
What's going on?

405
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:59,840
What's going on?

406
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,480
Someone is arrested.

407
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:06,640
It's you.

408
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:10,720
This is Ji Fangming,
who was guarding the Historical Archive.

409
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:17,760
We need your testimony and signature

410
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:20,320
regarding the fire.

411
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:21,960
I saw you guys hurrying here

412
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,400
when I was on my way

413
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,880
to the Shen Mansion.

414
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:33,040
Someone was burned to death
in the east of the city.

415
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,360
What?

416
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,080
Burned to death? Who was it?

417
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:37,400
It's one of us.

418
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,920
Officer Sun.

419
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,440
It was him?

420
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,440
Do you know about the Huo'e Sect?

421
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:47,760
It was Chen Huo'e

422
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,720
who gave him a punishment, you know?

423
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:50,920
A few days ago,

424
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,760
the fire at the Ministry of Justice

425
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:54,040
was a punishment

426
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,480
for Mrs. Shen.

427
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,920
- Mrs. Shen?
- She almost got burned to death.

428
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:01,720
Perhaps the White Ghost has done too much evil.

429
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:04,440
Retribution fell upon his wife.

430
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,200
Hearing wind and rain at night,

431
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,880
sitting still as a bell.

432
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,280
Stuffed from the night snack,

433
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:27,640
a few drinks are needed.

434
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:31,480
Did you figure out

435
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:32,920
where the powder is from?

436
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,720
It's from the Western Regions.

437
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,160
It's very mysterious.

438
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,320
I put in some serious effort

439
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:39,600
to figure it out.

440
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,720
Want a higher commission?

441
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:43,360
No way.

442
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:45,360
You took the trouble to memorize the code

443
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,720
and yet you came empty-handed?

444
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:47,760
In the worst case,

445
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:50,600
you could have brought me some wine.

446
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:53,000
If you admit that you are the famous

447
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,680
folksy detective Pan Chi,

448
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:56,000
I may consider

449
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,160
buying you the best

450
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:58,880
osmanthus wine in Xiang'an.

451
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:01,288
I am.

452
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,800
If I were the detective,

453
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:08,240
would you pay me more for my work?

454
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:10,400
You wish.

455
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,040
It sounds pretty good.

456
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:13,120
Hurry back home.

457
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,720
The Ghost Market is not safe these days.

458
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,800
Great Chief.

459
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,720
You asked me to look into Ji Fangming.

460
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:30,240
I found that he once
prescribed medicine for himself.

461
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:35,040
He's sick?

462
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:37,520
I didn't know he had studied the herbs.

463
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:38,600
I followed him

464
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,520
and found that he had health issues,

465
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:41,840
something chronic.

466
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,680
Take this prescription to the pharmacy.

467
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,040
I'd like to know

468
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,800
what sickness he has.

469
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:48,080
Are you suspecting him?

470
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:50,120
That fire in the Historical Archive

471
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:53,040
was set way too coincidentally.

472
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:07,560
The Great Chief must be busy.

473
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:08,640
I just came to ask

474
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,960
what tea he would like.

475
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,160
Please don't bother.

476
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:14,080
Miss Yun Que, please go back.

477
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,080
Did you find something

478
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,160
about the Jinxiu Workshop?

479
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,880
Miss, rest assured.

480
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:21,200
The Great Chief will inform you when necessary.

481
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:29,672
I've got something.

482
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,240
This powder

483
00:27:31,240 --> 00:27:32,720
is from a plant unique to

484
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:33,880
the Western Regions.

485
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:36,600
It produces a unique scent once burnt.

486
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:37,840
Those who smell it

487
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,360
become exceptionally excited

488
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:40,880
and even hallucinate.

489
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:43,120
It is said that if someone

490
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:44,480
implies something

491
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,800
to those who smell it,

492
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,160
it may induce an illusion

493
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:49,680
based on the description.

494
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:53,000
Is it available in the Ghost Market?

495
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,720
Not really.

496
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:56,160
It is said that this plant

497
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:58,360
may be common in the Western Regions,

498
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,040
but it's hard to survive

499
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:01,320
without the specific soil.

500
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,560
Therefore, for this powder

501
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:04,840
to create a strong hallucination,

502
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,880
one can't store it for too long.

503
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:07,920
Could it be that

504
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,040
someone has secretly

505
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:11,160
planted it in Xiang'an?

506
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,560
Is the information true?

507
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:17,480
I learned from my friend Pan Chi

508
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,600
in the Ghost Market.

509
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,200
The tips from him can't be wrong.

510
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:26,480
Do you know that Ji Fangming is ill?

511
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:32,640
You count on your connections

512
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:35,240
while neglecting the clues around you.

513
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,200
Back at Chen Shoujie's Mansion,

514
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,920
the way he showed up and his reactions

515
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,960
were strange.

516
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,080
Others were interested in

517
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:07,440
what happened in the house.

518
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,800
But he was curious about

519
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:11,800
our reactions to the incident.

520
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:14,408
Exactly.

521
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,520
And it occurs to me

522
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:24,640
that I've once smelled

523
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:27,400
a faint scent on Ji Fangming.

524
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,080
I didn't pay much attention to it.

525
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:31,200
Now that I think of it,

526
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,440
it was somewhat familiar

527
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,600
but not common.

528
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:39,280
I've only smelled it in one place.

529
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:41,720
Mingsheng Temple.

530
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:43,880
He's been there as well?

531
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:47,360
I told Chuichui to look into Ji Fangming

532
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:50,080
and inquire about his background.

533
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,560
He entered the Ministry of Justice

534
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:53,120
with someone's recommendation.

535
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:55,320
Guess who that person was.

536
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,920
Could it be…

537
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:00,160
That's right.

538
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:02,320
It was Chen Shoujie.

539
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:04,600
Apart from that,

540
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,600
he had a clean record,

541
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:09,840
nothing suspicious.

542
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:12,360
That makes it all the more suspicious.

543
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:15,360
There must be some secrets.

544
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:17,000
Chen Shoujie had kindly

545
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,480
recommended him to take on a job.

546
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,440
But that day at the crime scene,

547
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:24,880
he pretended not to know him.

548
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:27,800
Chen Shoujie had made recommendations.

549
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,680
I've looked into them.

550
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:33,920
Their paths never crossed.

551
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,240
That means

552
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:38,120
there is some middleman

553
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:40,480
that ties them together

554
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:43,680
and we haven't found out about it.

555
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:47,160
It seems

556
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:49,880
we have to ask them in person.

557
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:04,400
Mr. Ji, here.

558
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:07,560
Clerk Yan, this is…

559
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:10,240
Finally, I don't have to read

560
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,360
those random records anymore.

561
00:31:12,360 --> 00:31:15,840
So you've found the murderer?

562
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,320
Yes, that's right.

563
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:18,720
Chen Shoujie

564
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,560
committed all those crimes.

565
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:22,720
He played dumb and deceived everyone.

566
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:25,520
In fact, those were his confessions.

567
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:27,600
What? He confessed?

568
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:28,960
Yeah.

569
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,040
You know my husband.

570
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:33,880
The famous White Ghost.

571
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:34,960
In less than a day,

572
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:38,280
